{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place coriander seeds into mixing bowl and dry roast <b>2-3 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>. Allow to cool slightly, <strong>insert measuring cup<\/strong>, then mill <b>1 min\/speed 10<b>. Repeat milling as needed to achieve a fine powder consistency.","Add long red chillies, ginger, ground paprika, garlic cloves, lime zest, lime juice and lemongrass and chop <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Repeat process as needed to achieve a paste consistency.","Mix <b>1 min\/speed 4<b> slowly pouring oil onto measuring cup, letting it drizzle into mixing bowl to combine. Stop once all oil is incorporated. Use as needed."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 tbsp coriander seeds","8 long red chillies, deseeded if preferred, cut into pieces","4 cm cube fresh ginger, peeled","2 tbsp ground paprika","8 garlic cloves","4 limes, zest and juice only","4 stalks fresh lemongrass, white part only, cut into pieces","100 g peanut oil"]}],"id":"r68365","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-Q5d6Ylca1Ts\/XZaplJLg3oI\/AAAAAAAAhSY\/_h3cY_3hHfsQXrovVxOe-FWcffUzo6mIQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_3TFPYupPoIYUj5Dh.png","title":"Red Thai curry paste","publishedAt":"2014-09-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1 g","fat":"13 g","uom":"per 50 g","carbohydrates":"2 g","calories":"574 kJ \/ 137 kcal"},"usefulItems":"airtight container","hintsAndTricks":["Red Thai curry paste will keep for 2 - 3 weeks in the refrigerator if stored in an airtight container or can be frozen until use. Transfer into an ice cube tray and freeze for easy-to-use portions.","This recipe can be halved if a smaller quantity is required."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","15m","400 g"]}